    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Relatively small and narrow bookcases, often approximately 3 feet wide and 3 feet high, of the type used in the 18th and 19th century mercantile establishments for keeping account books.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000053014/Gloag and Edwards, Complete Dictionary of Furniture (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000053015/Haines Halsey and Tower, Homes of Our Ancestors in the Metropolitan Museum (1937)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Término usado a fines del siglo XVIII y a principios del siglo XIX para librerías relativamente pequeñas y angostas, de generalmente 3 pies de ancho y 3 pies de alto.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Term die wordt gebruikt in de late 18e en vroege 19e eeuw voor relatief kleine en smalle boekenkasten, over het algemeen ongeveer 1 meter (3 voet breed) en 1 meter (3 voet) hoog.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>相對較小而窄的書櫃，通常長寬大約各為3英尺，為西元十八及十九世紀時，商業機構用來保存帳冊的書櫃形式。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
